{"rendered": {"reason": {"raw": "trying out a different approach", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>trying out a different approach</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "description": {"raw": "Fix an issue with lights not casting shadows when there are more lights \\(shadow-casting \\+ non-shadow-casting\\) in the scene than the number of shadow maps specified in the compositor.\r\n\r\nApparently, just by having a shadow-casting directional light in the scene, shadows for other lights start working again. So the workaround to always create a directional light but initially set it as disabled, and later re-enabled it when user requests a directional light.\r\n\r\nHere\u2019s a screenshot showing the spot lights are now properly occluded and no longer leaks through the wall.\r\n\r\n![](data/bitbucket.org/repo/zq9ear/images/3787883042-spot_light_shadows.png)\r\n\u200c", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Fix an issue with lights not casting shadows when there are more lights (shadow-casting + non-shadow-casting) in the scene than the number of shadow maps specified in the compositor.</p>\n<p>Apparently, just by having a shadow-casting directional light in the scene, shadows for other lights start working again. So the workaround to always create a directional light but initially set it as disabled, and later re-enabled it when user requests a directional light.</p>\n<p>Here\u2019s a screenshot showing the spot lights are now properly occluded and no longer leaks through the wall.</p>\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"data/bitbucket.org/repo/zq9ear/images/3787883042-spot_light_shadows.png\" />\n\u200c</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "title": {"raw": "Ogre2: Fix spot light shadows", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Ogre2: Fix spot light shadows</p>", "type": "rendered"}}, "type": "pullrequest", "description": "Fix an issue with lights not casting shadows when there are more lights \\(shadow-casting \\+ non-shadow-casting\\) in the scene than the number of shadow maps specified in the compositor